    • Method Detail

      • layout

        abstract LAYOUT layout​(IndexDescriptor descriptor,
                       Path storeFile)
        Instantiates the Layout which is used in the index backing this native index provider.
        Parameters:
        descriptor - the IndexDescriptor for this index.
        storeFile - index store file, since some layouts may depend on contents of the header. If null it means that nothing must be read from the file before or while instantiating the layout.
        Returns:
        the correct Layout for the index.

      • getInitialState

        public InternalIndexState getInitialState​(IndexDescriptor descriptor,
                                          PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
        Description copied from class: IndexProvider
        Called during startup to find out which state an index is in. If InternalIndexState.FAILED is returned then a further call to IndexProvider.getPopulationFailure(IndexDescriptor, PageCursorTracer) is expected and should return the failure accepted by any call to IndexPopulator.markAsFailed(String) call at the time of failure.
        Specified by:
        getInitialState in class IndexProvider
        Parameters:
        descriptor - to get initial state for.
        cursorTracer - underlying page cursor tracer.
